replyContent: Hi Lillian. In the app, you can choose to rate some symptoms as "most days" and others as "only sometimes" - perhaps you accidentally marked fatigue as "only sometimes" when signing up? To change this, press your name in the top left of the home screen, press settings, and go to medical info. If this doesn't help, email us at support@human.health.

content: I'd like to be able to add my own unique symptoms. Important for me. Also I need to be able to just note when I take one pill (in response to a symptom) not beginning and ending days. That's not an option that I can see.
replyContent: Hey there! If you reach out to us at support@human.health, we can add your missing symptoms in a couple of minutes. You can mark your pills as "As needed" if they are one-offs. content: This was exactly what I was looking for in a medication and symptoms management app

I am really enjoying this app so far! I have tried to adapt other apps to track my symptoms, and it's always been a failure. I especially enjoyed that when setting it up, I can pick a diagnosis I already have, and it will suggest related symptoms for me. The symptoms get really specific, and I appreciate that. I wish there was a way to edit that an uptick in a 'symptom' is actually a good thing. When I'm having more repetitive speech and movement that means I'm doing better!

This is a great app all in all. So many symptoms and treatments are available, and the reminders really help my forgetful self stay on track with meds and such. One suggestion I have would be the option to track symptoms of "yesterday" or a day you missed. I think that would give a more accurate weekly report and allow people to reflect on the day's symptoms after they've woken up or if they're night owls like me and stay up past midnight lol.

Absolute waste of time.
replyContent: Hi Kyra, so sorry about your experience. I have let our team know about the issues with the URL - we really appreciate this feedback. Human is designed to help people track symptoms, and all types of treatments, including diets. You are right that we are not designed as a full-featured diet-tracking tool. We'll make this clearer in our messaging!
